    <fr:title text="De Morgan's Laws">De Morgan's Laws</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
  De Morgan's laws describe how negation interacts with conjunction and disjunction in propositional logic. They state that:
</html:p>
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[
  \begin {align*}
    \neg  (p \land  q) &\equiv  \neg  p \lor  \neg  q \\
    \neg  (p \lor  q) &\equiv  \neg  p \land  \neg  q
  \end {align*}
]]></fr:tex>
  </fr:mainmatter>
